The paper deals with analyzing the effect of social interference on online experiments, which falls under the category of social networks and information retrieval (cs.SI) and computational social science (cs.SOC). The methodology proposed involves graph clustering, which is a technique used in data science (cs.DS) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the use of Horvitz-Thompson estimator, which is a statistical inference method used in information theory (cs.IT).
